HEADWORD: Boletus
<hw>Bo*le"tus</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>boletus</ets>, Gr. <ets><?/</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
genus of fungi having the under side of the pileus or cap composed of a
multitude of fine separate tubes. A few are edible, and others very
poisonous.</def>⟦br⟧
